subject: HISTORY
text: Give the century, B.C. or A.D., of ten of the following, indicate who or what each was, and say why each is important in history. Answers must be written in the space provided after each name. Drake's Voyage round the World, St. Francis of Assisi, John Hampden, Kenneth MacAlpine, Michelangelo, The Marquis of Montrose, Sir Isaac Newton, The Peasants' Revolt, Cneius Pompeius (Pompey), The Battle of Salamis, The Battle of Stirling Bridge, The Treaty of Wedmore.
